The paper focuses on relation detection in natural language processing, which is a core topic in computational linguistics (cs.CL). The proposed method involves learning representation mapping using adversarial and reconstruction objectives, which are common techniques in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also deals with knowledge base question answering, which is related to information retrieval (cs.IR) and database systems (cs.DB).
